1 (3) (I) “UNLICENSED SETTING” MEANS A SETTING FOR AN
2 OUT–OF–HOME PLACEMENT THAT IS NOT LICENSED.
3 (II) “UNLICENSED SETTING” INCLUDES:
4 1. A HOTEL, MOTEL, OR SHORT–TERM RENTAL;
5 2. A SHELTER DESIGNATED TO MEET THE NEEDS OF A
6 CHILD WHO HAS RUN AWAY OR WHO IS HOMELESS; AND
7 3. AN OFFICE BUILDING OR OTHER NONRESIDENTIAL
8 ENVIRONMENT.
9 (III) “UNLICENSED SETTING” DOES NOT INCLUDE:
10 1. THE VOLUNTARY PLACEMENT OF A FORMER CINA;
11 OR
12 2. THE PLACEMENT OF A CHILD WITH:
13 A. AN INDIVIDUAL WHO IS A KINSHIP CAREGIVER OR
14 FOSTER PARENT OR WHO IS IN THE PROCESS OF APPLYING TO BE A KINSHIP
15 CAREGIVER OR FOSTER PARENT; OR
16 B. A PARENT, INCLUDING IN A FAMILY–BASED
17 RESIDENTIAL TREATMENT SETTING.
18 (b) (1) The Administration shall establish a program of out–of–home
19 placement for minor children:
20 (i) who are placed in the custody of a local department, for a period
21 of not more than 180 days, by a parent or legal guardian under a voluntary placement
22 agreement;
23 (ii) who are abused, abandoned, neglected, or dependent, if a
24 juvenile court:
25 1. has determined that continued residence in the child’s
26 home is contrary to the child’s welfare; and
27 2. has committed the child to the custody or guardianship of
28 a local department; or

4 HOUSE BILL 1559
1 (iii) who, with the approval of the Administration, are placed in an
2 out–of–home placement by a local department under a voluntary placement agreement
3 subject to paragraph (2) of this subsection.
4 (c) (1) [In] EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS
5 SUBSECTION, IN establishing the out–of–home placement program the Administration
6 shall:
7 [(1)] (I) provide time–limited family reunification services to a child
8 placed in an out–of–home placement and to the parents or guardian of the child, in order
9 to facilitate the child’s safe and appropriate reunification within a timely manner;
10 [(2)] (II) concurrently develop and implement a permanency plan that is
11 in the best interests of the child; and
12 [(3)] (III) provide training on an annual basis for the staff at each local
13 department who administer requests for voluntary placement agreements for children with
14 developmental disabilities or mental illnesses under subsection (b) of this section.
15 (2) THE OUT–OF–HOME PLACEMENT PROGRAM ESTABLISHED BY THE
16 ADMINISTRATION SHALL PROHIBIT THE PLACEMENT OF A CHILD IN AN UNLICENSED
17 SETTING.
