19 STATEWIDE ACCESS AND FULL IMPLEMENTATION BY 2030.
20 (B) ON OR BEFORE JANUARY 1, 2027, AND JANUARY 1, 2028, THE
21 INTERAGENCY COUNCIL SHALL REPORT ITS FINDINGS AND RECOMMENDATIONS TO
22 THE GOVERNOR, THE PLACEMENT MANAGER, AND, IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257
23 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY.
24 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Governor may transfer
25 positions and funds appropriated for positions from the Workgroup on Children in
26 Unlicensed Settings and Pediatric Hospital Overstays to the Governor’s Office for Children.
27 SECTION 4. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That Section 2 of this Act shall take
28 effect October 1, 2026. It shall remain effective for a period of 3 years and, at the end of
29 September 30, 2029, Section 2 of this Act, with no further action required by the General
30 Assembly, shall be abrogated and of no further force and effect.
31 SECTION 5. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, except as provided in Section
32 4 of this Act, this Act shall take effect June 1, 2026.

